# next.wadehammes.com handbook

Before **substantive** work—features, refactors, Prismic/CMS, Spirals, App Router or API routes, CI/env, analytics—read **`docs/handbook/README.md`** and the chapter that matches the task. Use **`docs/handbook/llms.md`** for a compact task→chapter map.

Follow documented patterns in the handbook.

**Keep docs accurate:** When a change would make the handbook wrong or incomplete (new flows, moved files, scaffold/convention changes, Prismic/parser patterns, Spirals behavior), update the relevant **`docs/handbook/*.md`** in the same PR when practical, or in a small follow-up right away.

You may skip a full handbook pass for **narrow** edits (typos, single obvious lines, mechanical fixes) that do not change behavior or documented expectations.
